{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f516-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"917"},"text":"§ 917.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional findings","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Congress finds that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f517-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" whales are a unique resource of great aesthetic and scientific interest to mankind and are a vital part of the marine ecosystem;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f518-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" whales have been overexploited by man for many years, severely reducing several species and endangering others;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f519-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the United States has extended its authority and responsibility to conserve and protect all marine mammals, including whales, out to a two hundred nautical mile limit by enactment of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.];"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f51a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the conservation and protection of certain species of whales, including the California gray, bowhead, sperm, and killer whale, are of particular interest to citizens of the United States;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f51b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" increased ocean activity of all types may threaten the whale stocks found within the two hundred-mile jurisdiction of the United States and added protection of such stocks may be necessary;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f51c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" there is inadequate knowledge of the ecology, habitat, requirements, and population levels and dynamics of all whales found in waters subject to the jurisdiction of the United States; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f51d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s917/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" further study of such matters is required in order for the United States to carry out its responsibilities for the conservation and protection of marine mammals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id78d4f51e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/532/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–532, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2491"},"text":"90 Stat. 2491","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/561/tII/s238/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–561, title II, § 238(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3300"},"text":"94 Stat. 3300","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/208/dA/tI/s101/a/tII/s211/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–208, div. A, title I, § 101(a) [title II, § 211(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3009"},"text":"110 Stat. 3009","children":[],"tail":", 3009–41.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id78d4f51f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id78d4f520-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id78d4f521-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act, referred to in par. (3), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/265"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–265","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-04-13"},"text":"Apr. 13, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/331"},"text":"90 Stat. 331","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 38 (§ 1801 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id78d4f522-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/208"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–208","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Magnuson-Stevens Fishery” for “Magnuson Fishery”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/561"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–561","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Magnuson Fishery Conservation and Management Act” for “Fishery Conservation and Management Act of 1976”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id78d4f523-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id78d4f524-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/208/dA/tI/s101/a/tII/s211/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–208, div. A, title I, § 101(a) [title II, § 211(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3009"},"text":"110 Stat. 3009","children":[],"tail":", 3009–41, provided that the amendment made by that section is effective 15 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id78d4f525-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/561/tII/s238/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–561, title II, § 238(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3300"},"text":"94 Stat. 3300","children":[],"tail":", provided that the amendment made by that section is effective 15 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1980","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id78d4f526-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/532/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–532, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2491"},"text":"90 Stat. 2491","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/94/532/s1"},"text":"“That this Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘Whale Conservation and Protection Study Act’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
